Nice — I built the complete, ready-to-drop Spring Boot project that uses plain REST calls to Camunda (no Zeebe client, no extra Camunda repo). You said:
	•	gRPC = localhost:8080 (you gave — I used it in YAML)
	•	REST = http://localhost:8080/engine-rest (I used this as the REST endpoint)
	•	Process id = Process_130bwuv (from earlier)

Drop these files into your project travel-backend (or replace contents) and run with mvn spring-boot:run.

⸻

